Many don’t understand and quick to make a statement or snap judgement. But as someone with a psychology background and is studying to be a counselling therapist - it is very clear to me how attachment has affected all the people on this show. Specifically how their earliest experiences of attachment with their caregiver or parents or earliest romantic relationships have affected them and shaped them. They have patterns of behaviours as every human does that is a result and product of their upbringing, environment, trauma, wounding, and conditioning. However, it is our responsibility to become aware of this but many never get that chance or know what to recognize or what to become aware of in the first place. Many don’t have access to mental health services which is messed up and totally wrong. However, this inevitably leads to these relationship dynamics that can potentially be chaotic, dysfunctional, emotionally unstable or draining, cause emotional turmoil and pain and wounding. We repeat the patterns of our childhood or earliest attachments. Books that can bring awareness are: Adults or Emotionally Immature Parents, Attached, Anxiously Attached, reading about attachment style and wounding, Internal Family Systems and books about trauma - especially childhood trauma and how it can is affect and shape us.
